6 AS INTRODUCED
7 A Resolution recognizing February as Black History
Month; recognizing the African American Community in
8 Oklahoma; and celebrating the contributions of
African Americans to the history of Oklahoma and the
9 United States.
10
11 WHEREAS, National African American History Month, also referred
12 to as African American History Month and Black History Month, is
13 annually observed in the month of February;
14 WHEREAS, the United States Congress passed Public Law 99-244 in
15 1986 to officially designate February as National Black History
16 Month in the United States to pay tribute and celebrate the
17 significant achievements and contributions made by Black Americans;
18 WHEREAS, Black History Month is celebrated in February to
19 commemorate the birthdays of Frederick Douglass and Abraham Lincoln,
20 both significant leaders in the abolition of slavery;
21 WHEREAS, numerous Oklahomans identify as African American;
22 WHEREAS, Black History Month serves as an opportunity to
23 acknowledge and recognize the role Black Americans have played in
