2 United States;
3 WHEREAS, the contributions of African Americans include but are
4 not limited to advancements in civil rights, business, education,
5 innovation, and leadership that have shaped this state and country
6 to what we know today;
7 WHEREAS, the State of Oklahoma acknowledges the impact and role
8 Black Americans have playing in shaping the culture, progress, and
9 history of our country; and
10 WHEREAS, it is important to recognize and celebrate the
11 significant achievements and progress made by groups of Americans
12 that strengthen our society as a whole; and
13 WHEREAS, the observance of Black History Month serves as an
14 opportunity for all citizens to celebrate the achievements of
15 African Americans, furthering that environment of togetherness.
16 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
17 OF THE 1ST SESSION OF THE 60TH OKLAHOMA LEGISLATURE:
18 THAT the month of February is formally recognized by the
19 Oklahoma House of Representatives as Black History Month.
20 THAT the Oklahoma House of Representatives recognizes the
21 contributions of Black Americans to the history of Oklahoma and the
22 United States.
